            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h3 class="my-3">Overview</h3>
                <p>Bhagalpur Ghanta Ghar, also known as the Clock Tower, is a significant landmark situated in the heart of Bhagalpur city in the Indian state of Bihar. This iconic structure, standing tall and illuminated at night, is surrounded by vendor stalls, vibrant markets, and bustling bazaars, making it a central hub of activity and commerce.</p>
                <h3 class="my-3">Historical Significance</h3>
                <p>Constructed during the British colonial period in the late 19th century, the Bhagalpur Ghanta Ghar was dedicated to King Edward VII of Britain. The clock tower's design showcases a blend of colonial and indigenous architectural styles, characterized by its imposing height, intricate carvings, and ornate embellishments. Over the years, the Ghanta Ghar has become an enduring symbol of Bhagalpur's rich history and cultural heritage.</p>
            </div>

